# Coffee-Sales-Dashboard
An Interactive Power BI dashboard that analyzes and visualizes coffee sales data. The project provides insights into sales performance, product trends, regional performance, and customer behavior to support data-driven decision-making.

üìçProject Overview
 This Power BI dashboard provides a comprehensive overview of a coffee shop‚Äôs sales, allowing users to explore key metrics such as:
 ‚Ä¢ Total customers
 ‚Ä¢ Revenue
 ‚Ä¢ Average Sales
 ‚Ä¢ Sum of quantity
 ‚Ä¢ Total Sales
 The dashboard is designed with usability in mind and includes slicers and filters for interactive exploration.

Key KPIs in the Dashboard:
‚úÖ Total Customers - Keep track of the overall customer base to assess market reach and growth.
‚úÖ Revenue - Monitor the total revenue generated, providing a high-level view of business performance.
‚úÖ Average sales - Analyze the average sales per transaction, offering insights into pricing strategies and customer spending behavior.
‚úÖ Sum of quantity - Track the total quantity of products sold, helping to understand volume and demand.
‚úÖ Total Sales - A comprehensive view of total sales, combining both revenue and quantity to assess business health.

Key Slicers in the Dashboard:
‚û°Ô∏è Coffee Type - Filter the data based on different coffee varieties, enabling analysis of sales trends per coffee type.
‚û°Ô∏è Roast Type - Drill down into the performance of various roast types, from light to dark roasts, to understand customer preferences.
‚û°Ô∏è Size - View sales data based on product size, helping businesses optimize inventory and sales strategies.
‚û°Ô∏è Country - Explore sales performance by country, enabling insights into regional differences and identifying growth opportunities.

The dynamic slicers and KPIs allow decision-makers to filter and explore the data based on different dimensions, providing a powerful tool for improving strategy and operational decisions.

 


